cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CYBER, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with Carrier Grade NAT (CGN) mechanisms used by ISPs to share a single IPv4 address across multiple customers. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as CGN can have security implications. Information Theory (cs.IT) is another possible category as the paper discusses the methodology used to detect CGNs. Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) is also a possible category as CGN can be used as a defense mechanism against cyber attacks. Finally, the paper may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category as it discusses the RIPE Atlas testbed, which is a global network of probes that measure Internet connectivity and reachability.
